I"u	<p>The Open Source Autonomous Vehicle Controller (OSAVC) project is designed to provide a real-time hardware controller adaptable to any vehicle type â€”aerial, terrestrial, marine, or extraterrestrial. The controller is designed to allow development of state estimation algorithms, sensor calibration methods and vehicle control models in a modular fashion, to allow easy switching of algorithms while retaining the hardware used.</p>

