</figcaption>
  
</figure>

<p>As a part of OSAVC, a novel method of real-time in-flight IMU calibration was developed. This work was funded by <strong>Google</strong> and was done as a part of the Google Summer of Code (GSoC) 2021 program,  with the <a href="https://asl.soe.ucsc.edu/"><strong>Autonomous Systems Lab of University of California, Santa Cruz</strong></a>, and the <a href="https://cross.ucsc.edu/"><strong>Center for Research in Open Source Software</strong></a>. The method used recursive least squares to continually optimize for IMU calibration parameters. The method was able to correct sudden changes in IMU calibration parameters and did not require any external mechanical setup. The work was also published in IEEE International Systems Conference in 2022.</p>

